56,0.07273357,0.04529965,-0.02319396,-0.04513024,0.01538911,0.03500870,-0.01708379,0.02736893,-0.06394561,0.05681727,-0.06048005,0.06253389,-0.10830426,-0.00442037,-0.01338415,-0.04859455,-0.07925045,-0.05304643,0.01703411,-0.03480312,-0.01623066,0.01125821,0.01074615,-0.00950249,-0.00735744,-0.00640694,0.00417687,0.00534978,-0.04857939,-0.01802107,-0.00023125,0.01432591,-0.01063802,-0.08279140,-0.05721010,-0.09322450,0.01422935,-0.01641357,-0.00855205,0.03329388,-0.03211466,-0.00650465]',E'Marking An Exchange As Routed\n\nAfter the gateway has routed a `ServerWebExchange`, it marks that exchange as "`routed`" by adding `gatewayAlreadyRouted`\nto the exchange attributes. Once a request has been marked as routed, other routing filters will not route the request again,\nessentially skipping the filter. There are convenience methods that you can use to mark an exchange as routed\nor check if an exchange has already been routed.\n\n* `ServerWebExchangeUtils.isAlreadyRouted` takes a `ServerWebExchange` object and checks if it has been "`routed`".\n* `ServerWebExchangeUtils.setAlreadyRouted` takes a `ServerWebExchange` object and marks it as "`routed`".','{"source": "spring-cloud", "version": "2024", "language": "java", "title": "Global Filters.Adoc", "section_title": "global-filters.adoc", "url": "https://github.com/spring-cloud/spring-cloud-gateway/blob/4.1.x/docs/modules/ROOT/pages/spring-cloud-gateway/global-filters.adoc", "topics": "spring,cloud,gateway,global,filters.adoc", "categories": "java,microservices,cloud,distributed"}');
